    "created_at": "2015-09-29T02:23:22Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-29T02:23:22Z",
    "body": "We have some issues with low level modules like serialport since the way they post events is keep waking up our Node.js message loop, fixing this is impossible or extremely hard.\n\nA popular way to work around this is to fork a Node process to use `serialport` and then post things back, in Electron `child_process.fork` should work perfectly in this case. Maybe this will work for you?\n"
  },
